Package org.neo4j.internal.id

Class DelayedBuffer<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.internal.id.DelayedBuffer<T>
  • public class DelayedBuffer<T>
extends Object
    Buffer of long values which can be held until a safe threshold is crossed, at which point they are released onto a Consumer. These values are held in chunk and each chunk knows which threshold is considered safe. Regular maintenance(PageCursorTracer) is required to be called externally for values to be released. This class is thread-safe for concurrent requests, but only a single thread should be responsible for calling maintenance(PageCursorTracer).

      • offer

        public void offer​(long value)
        Offers a value to this buffer. This value will at a later point be part of a buffered chunk, released by a call to maintenance(PageCursorTracer) when the safe threshold for the chunk, which is determined when the chunk is full or otherwise queued.

      • close

        public void close()
        Closes this buffer, releasing all offer(long) values into the Consumer. This class is typically not used in a scenario suitable for try-with-resource and so having it implement AutoCloseable would be more annoying
